        "title": "Add Zed provider with optional dashboard billing",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add a Zed provider using the editor's Keychain credentials and `GET /client/users/me` for plan, edit-prediction usage, and billing-cycle metadata.\n- Add optional dashboard billing through `zed.session` and `GET /frontend/billing/usage`; cookie usage defaults to **Off** and automatic import is Chrome-only.\n- Add provider settings, CLI/widget integration, docs, fixtures, and focused tests.\n\n## Maintainer rewrite\n\n- Removed the unrelated status-item placement changes from the contributor branch.\n- Preserved refresh cancellation and classified transport failures correctly.\n- Routed requests from Zed's configured `server_url`.\n- Bound custom-server credentials to the same HTTPS origin to prevent a settings-file change from forwarding a Keychain token elsewhere. Production and staging Zed servers retain their supported separate credential identifier.\n- Restored the widget Xcode project metadata to match `main`.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `swift test --filter 'Zed|BrowserCookieOrderStatusStringTests|ConfigurationDocsProviderIDTests'` (44 tests)\n- `make check`\n- local full-branch autoreview\n- implementation checked against upstream Zed credential storage and `/client/users/me` routing\n\n## Proof gate\n\nDo not merge until a maintainer has redacted real-account proof that a signed-in Zed editor refreshes the Keychain-backed account path successfully. If dashboard billing is intended to ship in the same PR, also prove the cookie-backed billing path with redacted output.\n\nRefs #846.\n",
